From f668575bb604a967f5939ab8c37cd2722c9f9f70 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Abraham Samuel Adekunle <abrahamadekunle50@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 5 Apr 2025 00:15:42 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] staging: rtl8723bs: Place constants on right side of comparison
Git-commit: f668575bb604a967f5939ab8c37cd2722c9f9f70
Patch-mainline: v6.16-rc1
References: jsc#PED-14425

Modify comparisons to place constants on the right hand side of expression
thereby following Linux kernel coding conventions.

Found and transformed by Coccinelle.

Semantic patch used for matching and transformation:

@@
constant K;
expression E;
@@
- K == E
+ E == K

Signed-off-by: Abraham Samuel Adekunle <abrahamadekunle50@gmail.com>
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/Z/B2LjtshZU6AX2f@ubuntu
Signed-off-by: Greg Kroah-Hartman <gregkh@linuxfoundation.org>
Acked-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

---
 .../staging/rtl8723bs/hal/HalBtc8723b2Ant.c   | 68 +++++++++----------
 1 file changed, 34 insertions(+), 34 deletions(-)

